</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
     3. HOW TO USE
     ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="how-to-use">
  <h2>🚀 How to Use</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Installation</h3>
    <pre>
# Build from source
./build-vsix.sh

# Install the VSIX
./install-extension.sh

# Reload VS Code
# Cmd+Shift+P → "Developer: Reload Window"</pre>

    <h3>Quick Start Workflow</h3>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h4>1. Create an Epic</h4>
        <p><code>Cmd+Shift+P</code> → "AI Command Center: Create Epic" → Enter name, description, priority</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h4>2. Add Stories & Tasks</h4>
        <p>Right-click an Epic → Create Story → Add Tasks. Full Epic → Story → Task hierarchy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h4>3. Connect Jira (Optional)</h4>
        <p>"AI Command Center: Configure Jira Integration" → Bidirectional sync with conflict resolution.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h4>4. Enable MCP Server</h4>
        <p>Settings → <code>aicc.mcp.enabled: true</code> → Connect Claude Desktop or other AI assistants.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <h4>5. Use AI Skills</h4>
        <p>50 skills auto-activate: image generation, video editing, translations, social media, commerce, and more.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

