<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
     11. SECURITY SCAN
     ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="security">
  <h2>🔒 Security Scan</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Vulnerability Summary</h3>
    <div class="card-grid" style="grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(130px,1fr));margin-bottom:16px;">
      <div class="stat-card" style="border-left:3px solid #f38ba8;"><div class="stat-value" style="font-size:1.4rem;color:#f38ba8">3</div><div class="stat-label">Critical</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card" style="border-left:3px solid #fab387;"><div class="stat-value" style="font-size:1.4rem;color:#fab387">4</div><div class="stat-label">High</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card" style="border-left:3px solid #f9e2af;"><div class="stat-value" style="font-size:1.4rem;color:#f9e2af">5</div><div class="stat-label">Medium</div></div>
      <div class="stat-card" style="border-left:3px solid #a6e3a1;"><div class="stat-value" style="font-size:1.4rem;color:#a6e3a1">3</div><div class="stat-label">Low</div></div>
    </div>

    <table>
      <tr><th>Severity</th><th>Finding</th><th>Location</th><th>Recommendation</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-critical"></span>Critical</span></td>
        <td><code>'unsafe-eval'</code> in Content Security Policy</td>
        <td>mainPanel.ts:499, mermaidPanel.ts:260, swagger.ts:74</td>
        <td>Remove <code>'unsafe-eval'</code> from CSP. Use nonce-based script loading for all panels. Refactor Mermaid/Swagger to load without eval.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-critical"></span>Critical</span></td>
        <td><code>child_process.exec()</code> without input sanitization</td>
        <td>securityManager.ts:11, aiKitManager.ts:6</td>
        <td>Replace <code>exec()</code> with <code>execFile()</code>. Validate all command arguments against allowlists. Use parameterized commands.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-critical"></span>Critical</span></td>
        <td><code>require('child_process')</code> in webview provider</td>
        <td>secondaryPanelProvider.ts:2317</td>
        <td>Move child_process calls to extension host. Use message passing to communicate with webview.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-high"></span>High</span></td>
        <td><code>innerHTML</code> assignment in webview</td>
        <td>mermaidPanel.ts:382</td>
        <td>Sanitize HTML content before innerHTML assignment. Use DOMPurify or template-based rendering.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-high"></span>High</span></td>
        <td><code>'unsafe-inline'</code> styles in CSP</td>
        <td>All panel CSP headers</td>
        <td>Use nonce-based inline styles or move styles to external stylesheet loaded via CSP source.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-high"></span>High</span></td>
        <td><code>new RegExp()</code> with user input (ReDoS risk)</td>
        <td>intakeManager.ts:309, kitConfigFormRenderer.ts:472</td>
        <td>Validate regex patterns before compilation. Set timeout limits. Use static patterns where possible.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-high"></span>High</span></td>
        <td>Swagger UI CSP has <code>'self'</code> with <code>'unsafe-eval'</code></td>
        <td>swagger.ts:74</td>
        <td>Load Swagger UI in a sandboxed iframe or use nonce-based loading.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-medium"></span>Medium</span></td>
        <td>Wide <code>connect-src</code> allows localhost connections</td>
        <td>All panel CSP headers</td>
        <td>Restrict to specific ports used by MCP server. Remove wildcard localhost patterns.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-medium"></span>Medium</span></td>
        <td><code>execSync</code> with 5-second timeout</td>
        <td>secondaryPanelProvider.ts:2321</td>
        <td>Use async <code>execFile</code> instead. Add proper error handling for timeouts.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-medium"></span>Medium</span></td>
        <td>Token handling in HTTP transport without encryption</td>
        <td>httpTransport.ts:220-222</td>
        <td>Ensure tokens are always transmitted over TLS. Add token expiration and rotation.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-medium"></span>Medium</span></td>
        <td>Regex exec loops without lastIndex reset</td>
        <td>smartContextEngine.ts (multiple)</td>
        <td>Reset regex lastIndex before loops or use matchAll() instead.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-medium"></span>Medium</span></td>
        <td>No rate limiting on webview message handler</td>
        <td>secondaryPanelProvider.ts</td>
        <td>Add message throttling to prevent DoS via rapid message flooding.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-low"></span>Low</span></td>
        <td>19 console.log statements in production code</td>
        <td>Various src/ files</td>
        <td>Replace all console.log with Logger instance. Add ESLint rule to prevent console usage.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-low"></span>Low</span></td>
        <td>Worker-src blob: in CSP</td>
        <td>mainPanel.ts, mermaidPanel.ts</td>
        <td>Restrict to specific worker scripts or use nonce-based worker loading.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="severity"><span class="severity-dot sev-low"></span>Low</span></td>
        <td>Frame-src allows localhost connections</td>
        <td>All panel CSP headers</td>
        <td>Restrict frame-src to only required origins.</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
     12. PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS
     ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="performance">
  <h2>⚡ Performance Analysis</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <h3>Performance Findings</h3>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Area</th><th>Finding</th><th>Impact</th><th>Recommendation</th></tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">High Impact</span></td>
        <td><strong>Monolithic extension.ts</strong> — 1,735 lines in single activation function</td>
        <td>Slow activation, blocks VS Code startup</td>
        <td>Lazy-load modules. Use activation events for specific features. Split into feature modules.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-red">High Impact</span></td>
        <td><strong>secondaryPanelProvider.ts</strong> — 3,090 lines, largest file</td>
        <td>High memory usage, complex state management</td>
        <td>Split into per-tab providers. Use component-based architecture. Implement virtual scrolling.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Medium</span></td>
        <td><strong>Full re-render on ideation filter</strong> — innerHTML replacement on each keystroke</td>
        <td>UI jank, dropped frames</td>
        <td>Implement virtual DOM diffing or targeted DOM updates. Debounce filter input.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Medium</span></td>
        <td><strong>Synchronous file I/O</strong> — execSync used in webview provider</td>
        <td>Blocks extension host thread</td>
        <td>Replace all execSync with async alternatives. Use worker threads for heavy I/O.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Medium</span></td>
        <td><strong>No caching in MCP tools</strong> — Planning data re-read on each request</td>
        <td>Redundant file reads, slow responses</td>
        <td>Implement LRU cache with file watcher invalidation. Cache hot planning data in memory.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Low</span></td>
        <td><strong>9,014 lines of media JS</strong> — All loaded upfront</td>
        <td>Initial load time for webviews</td>
        <td>Code-split JS by tab. Lazy-load tab content. Minify production builds.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Low</span></td>
        <td><strong>1,016 async functions</strong> — Not all have try-catch</td>
        <td>Unhandled promise rejections</td>
        <td>Add global unhandled rejection handler. Ensure all async functions have error boundaries.</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

