<!-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
     20. PRIORITY ACTIONS
     ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section id="priority-actions">
  <h2>🚨 Priority Actions — Ordered by Severity</h2>
  <div class="card">
    <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">The following actions are prioritized by severity and impact. Address critical security issues first, then quality, then feature improvements.</p>

    <div class="priority-list">
      <div class="priority-item" style="border-left:3px solid #f38ba8;">
        <div>
          <h4>Remove <code>'unsafe-eval'</code> from all CSP policies</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-secondary);"><span class="badge badge-red">Critical Security</span> — mainPanel.ts, mermaidPanel.ts, swagger.ts</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;">Refactor Mermaid and Swagger UI to load without eval. Use nonce-based script loading. This is the #1 security vulnerability.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="priority-item" style="border-left:3px solid #f38ba8;">
        <div>
          <h4>Replace <code>exec()</code> with <code>execFile()</code> and sanitize inputs</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-secondary);"><span class="badge badge-red">Critical Security</span> — securityManager.ts, aiKitManager.ts, secondaryPanelProvider.ts</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;">Command injection risk. Use parameterized commands. Move child_process out of webview provider.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="priority-item" style="border-left:3px solid #f38ba8;">
        <div>
          <h4>Validate RegExp patterns before compilation</h4>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;color:var(--text-secondary);"><span class="badge badge-red">Critical Security</span> — intakeManager.ts, kitConfigFormRenderer.ts</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.85em;">ReDoS vulnerability. Sanitize user-provided patterns. Add timeout to regex operations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

